The article announces three nominations that have been sent to the Senate. John P. Howard, III has been nominated to be an Associate Judge of the District of Columbia Court of Appeals for a term of fifteen years, replacing Kathryn A. Oberly who has retired. Deven J. Parekh has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the United States International Development Finance Corporation for a term of three years. This is a new position. Vijay Shanker has been nominated to be an Associate Judge of the District of Columbia Court of Appeals for a term of fifteen years, replacing John R. Fisher who is retiring.